Deck total: 70    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> *UPDATE ONE*<br>
"narya" Why? it does not do enough for me to use a card slot for it. I can remove burdens with Sam and I don&#39;t really need the extra vitality, it would be nice but just not worth the card slot for this deck.<br>
*END UPDATE ONE*<br>
<br>
You should bid 5-6 and sometime 7. You want to go first, but if you are out bid and your opponent is not using the Inn, sub Arwen out for Sam.<br>
<br>
Fellowship:<br>
This fellowship is versatile and very tough&#8230; it generally handles all shadow strategies well. Pull Sam (providing you go first or you opponent is using the Inn as well) drop what you can and move, always try to double move to the first sanctuary. You want to move from one to three, three to four, four to six, six to eight, and from eight to nine (that&#8217;s the best way, but some games just don&#8217;t go the way you plan. So I don&#8217;t worry if I can&#8217;t make it like that). You do not want to go super fellowship until site six or so, this is the way I like to use my fellowship. Don&#8217;t play a sixths companion unless you can drop a seventh. Always stay at four vs. Uruk-hai until site six, then go to seven or more companions if you can, that way you can run to site eight (if you can&#8217;t then just stick with the strong guys, Gandalf and Aragorn). The reason I use the four copies of Aragorn and Gandalf plus their gear is, that the super fellowship (as I use it) is a late game clincher or backup plan if something goes wrong big time.<br>
<br>
Shadow:<br>
Uruk-hai are the best right now! And the only minions I have ever played, that has changed&#8230; but with bad results.  Not really much special about my shadow. Just play them like most other Uruk-hai shadow sides.<br>
<br>
Site choices:<br>
Site one: pulls Sam<br>
Site two: no Stealth cards<br>
Site three: move limit plus one<br>
Site four: no roaming for my Uruk-hai<br>
Site five: like there&#8217;s a choice<br>
Site six: a neutral site (I like Caras Galadhon to but I did not play it in day one or two)  <br>
Site seven: Uruks do not like archery<br>
Site seven: nine twilight<br>
Site nine: fierce Uruk-hai if I don&#8217;t have Saruman<br>
<br>
Card choices:<br>
<br>
Why am I running the new Galadriel?<br>
She is good for this deck and has saved games for me. And I don&#8217;t like loosing my allies at the Confluence, which she can stop be pulling my site seven. She can heal any elf and there are six elves in the deck including herself.<br>
<br>
Why only two Sarumans?<br>
I did not want to add another card or take one out, so I settled on two, which worked fine as you well know.<br>
<br>
Why Bounder and not Bolger?<br>
Bolger is great and would be a good addition to the deck, but Bounder has saved so many games for me it isn&#8217;t right! Including my first game against John Arendt!<br>
<br>
This is also the same deck I played in day one, other then I could not get my hands on a fourth Troop so I used a fighter and in the place of one of the No Business I used a Battle Cry.<br>
<br>
That&#39;s about does it! The deck works awesome and I beat some great players with it, both in day one and two. Thanks for reading!<br>
<br>
